 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rojserbest', 'comment_id': 973190631.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-18 19:32:51+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "So here's our comment style, if I'm not wrong:
 - Starts with uppercase letter if the comment is a sentence.
 - Ends with a period if the comment is the sentence.
 - The above 2 styles aren't applied to inline comments.
 - Won't start with an uppercase letter or end with a period if the comment is not a sentence.
 
When a comment is a sentence in this case? When it includes a verb.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'KnorpelSenf', 'comment_id': 973283977.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-18 21:25:14+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'Good job, you two!

@username_0 please consider adding suggestions to a batch and then committing once. This will save us from having a bunch of similar commits, which makes it easier to review.

Will review more thoroughly when out of draft state.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rojserbest', 'comment_id': 973766421.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-19 05:28:02+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Adding suggestions to my own changes?', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'KnorpelSenf', 'comment_id': 974004318.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-19 11:49:27+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'When going through another person's review, instead of clicking "commit suggestion" 22 times, go to the files tab, then click "add suggestion to batch" 22 times, and perform a single commit that collects all changes.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
