 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'KnorpelSenf', 'comment_id': 975967905.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-22 22:19:28+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "Thanks for another thorough review! @username_0 I'd apply every suggestion I didn't comment on, unless you have objections. They make sense to me.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'KnorpelSenf', 'comment_id': 976423587.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-23 11:29:01+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "There are a lot of nit-picks in here, so just be sure that you're enjoying micro-optimising language as much as I do. It should not feel like a waste of time to anyone :)

I'll let you two decide on the exact conventions we use, and where to apply them. Just be sure to ping me once you agreed on stuff, so that I can
- adapt to the new rules when writing future articles, and
- make sure that both languages have the same code examples.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rojserbest', 'comment_id': 976549612.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-23 13:40:16+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Comment rules:
 - Start with an uppercase letter and include a period at the end if the comment included a sentence, this doesn't apply for inline comments.
 - Inline comments start with a lowercase and won't have periods in their end in any way.

List rules:
 - List items have nothing in common between them, No need for ",".', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rojserbest', 'comment_id': 976551113.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-23 13:41:21+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': '@username_1, the above is everything so far.', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rojserbest', 'comment_id': 976569313.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-23 13:54:16+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "And we're not forced to follow those instructions everytime, we should follow them in regular times only. For example, if we needed to have more clarity somewhere, we can break them,", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'KnorpelSenf', 'comment_id': 976606617.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-23 14:22:21+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'Understood. Regarding lists, I tend to write sentences with an enumeration that is simply formatted as a list. Example:

grammY is
- simple,
- fast, and
- powerful

and therefore a good choice for your bot.

Would you advise to rather break the rule, or to avoid such sentences?', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'rojserbest', 'comment_id': 976646608.0, 'datetime': '2021-11-23 14:42:11+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "I don't know where you took that style from, but I haven't seen splitting a sentence with a list like you do throughout my life.

I'd just write:

grammY is:
 - grammY
 - Simple
 - Fast
 - Powerful
 - Stunning", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
